{"id":"ameen-rihani--poetry","title":"Poetry","titleAlpha":"poetry","author":"Ameen Rihani","language":"en","description":"A collection of Ameen Rihani's poetry.","longDescription":["Born in Lebanon and brought to the United States by his father as a teenager, Ameen Rihani was a pioneer in the literary movement of Mahjar (Arab diaspora) literature. During his lifetime, he published two volumes of original English-language poetry, titled Myrtle and Myrrh (1905) and A Chant of Mystics and Other Poems (1921). Major themes explored in Rihani's poetry include Orientalism, mysticism, and cultural encounters between East and West. This Standard Ebooks edition presents both of Rihani's poetry collections in one volume."],"year":2023,"genres":["poetry"],"rights":"The source text and artwork in this ebook are believed to be in the United States public domain; that is, they are believed to be free of copyright restrictions in the United States. They may still be copyrighted in other countries, so users located outside of the United States must check their local laws before using this ebook. The creators of, and contributors to, this ebook dedicate their contributions to the worldwide public domain via the terms in the [CC0 1.0 Universal Public Domain Dedication](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/).","publisher":"Standard Ebooks","source":{"isUrl":true,"value":"https://standardebooks.org/ebooks/ameen-rihani/poetry"},"series":null,"part":0,"chapters":[{"id":"001","title":"Salaam - From Syria to America","length":2821,"skip":false},{"id":"002","title":"Ever to Be","length":979,"skip":false},{"id":"003","title":"Upon the Peak of Sanneen","length":2084,"skip":false},{"id":"004","title":"The Philistine","length":634,"skip":false},{"id":"005","title":"My Burnoose","length":671,"skip":false},{"id":"006","title":"A Spring Dirge","length":598,"skip":false},{"id":"007","title":"Fardi wa Nafli","length":1899,"skip":false},{"id":"008","title":"Adele","length":596,"skip":fal